'Phe ALBINUS, line 466, whose hospitality Rutilius enjoyed at his villa near Vada, and who succeeded Rutilius as Prefect of the City in 414,1 was probably Caecina Decius Acinatius Albinus, who seems to have been the son of Caecina Decius Albinus, Prefect of the City in 402, and grandson of Caecina Albinus, the friend of Symmachu8‚ whom Macrobius represents as taking part in the discussion in his Saturnalia, 1, 12. This Caecina Decius Acinatius Albinus probably enjoyed the honour of being Prefect of Rome a second time in 426. He was Praetorian Prefect of Italy in 443 and again in 447.
